{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e4325b1e-6327-4e49-b574-34a2de3fb1ec","content":"It's a simple change. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, so just removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is enough.\n2. **Run tests differently** — use `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since it now produces an executable.\n3. **CLI differences** — some VSTest CLI options (e.g. `--filter`) work the same, but platform-specific options use `--` syntax (e.g. `dotnet test -- --filter \"Name=MyTest\"`).\n4. **Check for VSTest-specific dependencies** — if you use custom adapters, `.runsettings` features, or VSTest-only extensions, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"83909d52-d02f-4bd5-9bab-732dcbc52871","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty and there's no relevant content in the repository. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and the migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":427,"requestId":"703A:1CDC41:E053EF4:F686D47:69F2A848"},"id":"6721ff65-0af6-424f-9549-55554d269c66","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:54:41.531Z","parentId":"170e281b-16af-43b1-b324-c5dc0fbc892b"}
